These mushrooms were found inside a ring of Redwood trees when for a moment a beam of sunlight shone upon them. Otherwise, the color of these mushrooms blended almost perfectly with the Redwood duff. The cap surface was dry and had a fine pebbly texture, and the stipes were dry, but slick, and almost felt like plastic. Also, the stipes were also had a very flattened shape. Their odor was unpleasant, although I can't find the words to describe it. Perhaps slightly burnt plastic.
